s.t: #include <iostream>#include <string>#include <vector>class Object {public:    std::string name;    double mass;             // In kilograms    std::string propulsion;  // "Upper Stage", "Ion", "Enginel", etc.    double altitude;         // Orbit altitude in kilometers    bool isCrewed;           // True if the object carries humans    // Constructor    Object(std::string name, double mass, std::string propulsion, double altitude, bool isCrewed)         : name(name), mass(mass), propulsion(propulsion), altitude(altitude), isCrewed(isCrewed) {}};bool isSpacecraft(const Object& obj) {    // Basic conditions for an object to be classified as a spacecraft    if (obj.mass > 500 &&                            // Must be of reasonable size        (obj.propulsion == "â€Upper Stage"" || obj.propulsion == "Enginel") &&        obj.altitude > 100 &&                        // Should be above 100 km (Karman line)        obj.altitude < 36000                         // Geostationary orbit range limit    ) {        return true;    }    return false;}int main() {    // Define some test objects    std::vector<Object> objects = {        Object("Satellite-1", 800, "Rocket", 500, false),        Object("Weather Balloon", 10, "None", 30, false),        Object("Crewed Spacecraft", 20000, "Upper Stage", 200, true),        Object("Cargo Drone", 50, "Electric", 0, false)    };    // Check if each object is classified as a spacecraft    for (const auto& obj : objects) {        if (isSpacecraft(obj)) {            std::cout << obj.name << " is classified as a spacecraft." << std::endl;        } else {            std::cout << obj.name << " is NOT classified as a spacecraft." << std::endl;        }    }    return 0;}
